<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / London Stock Exchange: All-time peak in Shell
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY.
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SURGE in Royal Dutch stock in the US overnight and on the Amsterdam market
early yesterday, which drove the shares up to a record high, promoted a
similar wave of support for Shell Transport shares, which raced ahead to an
all-time peak of 628p, prior to closing a net 12 up at 627p. Turnover was a
healthy 5.2m shares.
Apart from the impact of Royal Dutch's performance, Shell's strength came
from a general groundswell of international buying, after last week's round
of presentations by the company in Europe and ahead of a presentation to UK
analysts on Monday.
Dealers said the market had been overwhelmed by big buying interest and
heavy arbitrage business carried out by four big market players from the US.
'The market was caught short and spent most of yesterday chasing its tail in
Shell,' said one marketmaker. In its recent buy note on Shell, Strauss
Turnbull said it expected Shell 'to embark on an accelerated programme of
cost-cutting, via redundancies'.
</TEXT>
