<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Fine Decor gains listing through Pounds
10.7m placing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FINE DECOR, the wallpaper designer, manufacturer and distributor came to
market yesterday through a placing of 5.39m ordinary shares at 210p each,
valuing the Cheshire-based group at Pounds 26.2m.
The company demerged from Boots in 1989 via a management buy-out, six months
after the chemist and DIY business acquired it as part of Ward White.
The placing raised about Pounds 10.7m in net proceeds, of which Pounds 4.6m
will be used to repay company debt with the balance representing shares sold
by existing institutional shareholders.
None of the directors disposed of shares, they retain 3.63m, representing a
29.1 per cent stake.
Mr Harry Morgan, chief executive, who previously spent 16 years with
Unilever, said the proceeds of the placing would give the group greater
flexibility to finance growth and that the listing will give it access to a
wider capital market.
He added: 'Since the buy-out, we have achieved strong growth in sales,
profits and market share, despite severe recessionary conditions in most of
the group's markets. The combination of these markets moving out of
recession and a recovery in the number of house sales is expected to have a
beneficial impact on the group.
The directors have forecast operating profits of not less than Pounds 1.62m
for the first half to July 31, against Pounds 1.32m in the comparable
period.
They expect to recommend total dividends for the current year of not less
than 7.5p.
</TEXT>
