<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Interest cut gives boost to Caffyns
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Reduced exceptional costs and interest charges helped Caffyns, the motor
dealer, expand pre-tax profits from Pounds 63,000 to Pounds 262,000 in the
year ended March 31.
Turnover fell from Pounds 127.8m to Pounds 123.9m reflecting the closure of
four branches, and trading profit was cut from Pounds 1.77m to Pounds 1.55m.
Interest charges were Pounds 1.16m (Pounds 1.47m) mainly as a result of a
reduction in the stocking of new cars. Several manufacturers have introduced
new systems whereby they stand much of that cost and in return reduce the
dealers' margins in an attempt to forego heavy discounting.
Currently, the group was in negotiation to restructure its activities in the
Brighton and Hove area.
Negotiations were also in progress with Shell about future arrangements
regarding the petrol stations operated under the Shell Share franchise.
Earnings per share were 0.8p (losses 5.6p). The recommended final dividend
is 6.5p for an unchanged total of 11.5p.
</TEXT>
