<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Sanderson Elect static at Pounds 1.8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite the economic climate and a disappointing contribution from
associates, Sanderson Electronics held first half pre-tax profits at Pounds
1.8m.
The group, which supplies a range of computer solutions and maintenance and
support services, lifted turnover 14 per cent to Pounds 12.1m and trading
profit 8 per cent to Pounds 1.97m. Associates' contribution fell to Pounds
13,000 (Pounds 189,000).
Mr Paul Thompson, chairman, said 74 per cent of overheads were covered by
annually recurring revenues from maintenance, software licence fees and
service and support contracts, which currently provide turnover of about
Pounds 10m per year.
Profit reflected an 8 per cent increase in the UK although five of the
subsidiaries were still operating at 'well below peak levels of
profitability'.
Earnings per share came to 14.2p (16p) after a higher tax rate. The second
interim dividend of 4.5p makes 9.9p (9p).
