<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Revamped Albrighton cuts losses
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ALBRIGHTON, the heavily-restructured quarrying group, reported a sharply
reduced deficit over the 12 months to March 31.
On turnover of Pounds 2.45m (Pounds 2.53m from continuing operations) and
after reduced interest charges of Pounds 277,000 (Pounds 684,000), losses
before tax were reduced to Pounds 358,000 (Pounds 14.1m restated for FRS 3).
The USM-quoted group has made a number of disposals over the past two years
to reduce debt.
Following the Pounds 3.2m acquisition of five quarries and two masonry
processing plants late last year from Tarmac - the acquisition was
'substantially completed and going well' - it now focused on natural
dimensional stone products.
Mr Humphrey Wood, chairman, said the outcome was affected by rationalisation
and redundancy costs; the group still had a bad debt problem and trading
activity was at a low level, although the current year had got off to a
'promising' start.
Losses per share were 0.6p (225.1p).
