<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / Letter: In control of directors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr T G TREFGARNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, The proposal by Postel to vote against the re-election of directors who
are on rolling service agreements longer than 12 months is welcome ('Pension
fund move to limit directors' contracts', June 5). However, voting such
directors off the board would itself be a breach of many service agreements,
so triggering the excessive pay-offs Postel's move seeks to deter.
Short of new legislation or stock exchange rules, shareholders should ensure
company boards are made up of a majority of directors prepared to take
shareholder opinion into account before such agreements are entered into.
T G Trefgarne,
21 Bishops Mansions,
Bishops Park Road,
London SW6 6DZ
