</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE income of chartered surveyors and commercial estate agents fell by 6 per
cent in the past year, says a survey published by Economic Development
Briefing, a research group.
The survey found that the UK's largest 3,000 property clients cut their
spending on property services in the past 12 months from Pounds 903m to
Pounds 843m. The fee income for agency and financial services work fell by
about a quarter.
