<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 93 / Kurdish rebels declare war on Turkey
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ANKARA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Kurdish rebels declared all-out war on Turkey yesterday and the government
vowed to destroy them, setting the stage for another bloody summer in the
south-east, Reuter reports from Ankara.
Mr Abdullah Ocalan, head of the Kurdistan Workers' party (PKK), said he was
resuming the military struggle because Ankara had ignored the unilateral
ceasefire the PKK declared in March.
Some 330 people, most of them PKK rebels, have been killed in the mainly
Kurdish south-east since the PKK seized and killed 33 soldiers in May.
