<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 93 / Walesa bid to avert pay strike
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PRESIDENT Lech Walesa will meet Solidarity leaders today to discuss pay
demands over which the trade union is threatening to call a general strike,
Reuter reports.
According to Mr Marian Krzaklewski, Solidarity chairman, the talks in Warsaw
will cover union demands for pay rises in the public sector and changes in
economic policy. 'I do not expect that after these talks everything will
change in Poland, but we would be satisfied if we got a positive response to
some of our demands,' he said.
Solidarity helped bring down Poland's government last month by calling a
parliamentary confidence vote after Ms Hanna Suchocka, the prime minister,
refused their pay demands. The union repeated threats to call a nationwide
strike if its demands were not met after Mr Walesa dissolved parliament and
asked Ms Suchocka to stay on until elections on September 19.
</TEXT>
