THE international capital markets continue to show a steady stream of
international equity offerings and equity-linked deals from corporate names
around the globe.
Woolworths, the Australian retailer, will open its ADollars 2.4bn share
issue to the public tomorrow, with the shares expected to be priced at
between ADollars 2.15 and ADollars 2.45.
Meanwhile, investment bankers expect the heavy flow of issues from Latin
American to continue. While investors are focusing on the sale of 35 per
cent of YPF, the Argentine state-owned oil group, other names are expected
to tap the markets, possibly before the summer holiday season.
