FT  09 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Automotive Prods returns to black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Automotive Products, which serves the car and aircraft industries and is
owned by the Guthrie Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of BBA, returned
to profits in 1992 with Pounds 16.2m pre-tax.
Previously the deficit was Pounds 1.1m after a Pounds 6.8m loss on sale and
termination of businesses.
Directors said there were isolated instances of buoyancy but the long-term
recovery had not materialised. Turnover moved up to Pounds 283.5m (Pounds
269.2m).
