up to 6,000 of the UK's 18,500 sites over the next two to three years.
He considered the prospective fall in sites 'alarmist and wildly
exaggerated' but added that the adverse conditions presented Frost with
expansion opportunities as there were a record number of sites for
acquisition in solicitors' hands.
